      "side": 1,
      "message": "To clarify one point:\n\n\u003c\u003c So do we have back-to-back return statements now? The new ones you added, plus the ones generated by writeProcessorFunction? \u003e\u003e\n\nThat\u0027s not right. SkSL will actually fail shader compilation with \"unreachable\" if you have two returns in a row.\n\nThe end result of this CL is intended to be the exact same shader text as before; the difference is that previously, `return sk_OutColor;` was added implicitly by code, and now written out explicitly in each FP file:\n\nhttps://skia-review.googlesource.com/c/skia/+/307705/6/src/gpu/glsl/GrGLSLFragmentShaderBuilder.cpp\n\n(A special exception is made for Runtime Effects, where we continue appending `return sk_OutColor;` to avoid breaking Chrome.)\n\nI would not expect any significant changes in perf/complexity/etc from this change. At the end of the day, it should be compiling the same shader text as before. It was just assembled differently.",
      "parentUuid": "d0f06a0b_8291dadf",
      "revId": "be0d16720e47925ec18a50354dfb9821c3629a91",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": false
    },
